# Harness Operations

Status: live

This directory is the operating layer for agent-assisted work in {{project_name}}.
It keeps instructions, state, verification, scope, and lifecycle handoff visible
in repo files instead of hidden in chat history.

Platform contract: {{platform_contract_summary}}

## Purpose

Make each coding session restartable, scoped, and verifiable. Agents should
find the objective, know what they may change, run the right checks, and leave
evidence for the next session.

## Five Core Subsystems

Harness = instructions + tools + environment + state + feedback. Missing any
one of these makes the harness incomplete. Keep instruction files map-like,
tool access least privilege but useful, environment facts self-describing,
state current, and verification commands explicit. Treat feedback as the
highest-return repair target.

| Subsystem | Primary Files |
| --- | --- |
| Instructions | `{{agent_file}}`, platform routers |
| Tools | `init.sh`, `init.ps1`, optional owner tools |
| Environment | manifests, component inventory, dependency policy |
| State | `feature_list.json`, `current-state.md`, roadmap |
| Feedback | verification matrix, sensor registry, evidence log |

## Effective Agent Boundary

The model is the LLM. The effective coding agent is the model plus the harness:
system prompts, instructions, shell/file tools, git access, filesystem scope,
startup scripts, verification commands, stop hooks, lint/sensor checks,
workflow permissions, and evaluator loops. Changing any of these changes effective agent behavior and needs scope, verification, and rollback.

